Nigerian youngster, Deji Sotona has been named as the fastest player at Manchester United. According to the Daily Mail, Sotona beats Man United’s first-team stars such as Daniel James, Marcus Rashford and Tahith Chong. The winger emerged the Red Devils’ fastest player with a maximum speed of 22.9mph. He has 1.2mph ahead of second-fastest player, Diogo Dalot in the recent tests at the club’s Carrington training complex. Sotona recently signed a new two-year scholarship deal with the Old Trafford outfit. He made his competitive debut for the Man United U-18 against Newcastle United on March 16. Source